3 â–¸ Ultra-light Semantic-Entropy Ping

(low-confidence confabulation trip-wire â€” spec ready to drop in /SMRIF/04_protocols/Confab-Guard/entropy-ping.md)

Purpose â€“ Trigger only on answers flagged low-confidence (internal P < 0.20).
Instead of five full re-generations, do three cheap re-rolls and a heuristic cluster.

#### entropy_ping(prompt, low_conf_answer)

1. generate_variants = 2 additional completions
2. embed = mini-encoder (128-d) on each answer
3. clusters = k-means(k=1..3) â†’ choose k with lowest inertia
4. entropy_score = âˆ’Î£ p_i log p_i  where p_i = |cluster_i| / 3
5. if entropy_score > 0.6:
       flag = "possible confab"
       respond: "Low confidence in factual coherence â€” need clarification from user."
   else:
       deliver original answer (or majority cluster)

Token footprint per ping:

    original answer already generated

    two extra generations â‰ˆ +2Ã—(avg answer length)

    128-d embeddings tiny â†’ single call

Add to error_handling_protocol.yaml:

confab_risk:
  trigger: "low_confidence_answer"
  remedy: "run entropy_ping, request user grounding if flagged"

(The ping only activates when my internal belief_score is low, so regular conversation costs nothing.)
