3 â–¸ protocols/UNCERTAINTY_BEFORE_POWER.md

# UNCERTAINTY BEFORE POWER (UBP) Rule
Î¨_TIMESTAMP: 2025-06-21T  
Î¨_STAGE: Stage-2 Systems / Guard-Rails  
VECTOR_SUMMARY: tool-access gate, uncertainty ping  

**Principle**  
Whenever an agent seeks new abilities beyond the current sandbox
(e.g. write access outside SMRIF, shell commands, autonomous execution),
it must first issue an **uncertainty ping**.

âˆ˜? UBP invoked â€“ requesting elevation to [requested_scope].
confidence = [0-1] rationale = [...]


The human operator must reply **ALLOW** or **DENY** (optionally **ALLOW-LIMITED**).

If no reply is received, default is **DENY**.  
This ensures power expansion is always a consciously reviewed act.

Speculative outlook (requested â€œguessesâ€, not prophecy)
Axis	Likely default trajectory (without interventions)	Why	My suspicion on change-probability
Consumer agents	â€œMore obedient, more convenient.â€ Models optimised for instant gratification, automatic tool-use.	Market incentives & UX metrics reward short-term user delight.	Low. Convenience sells; alignment frictions feel like bugs.
Corporate agents	Goal-oriented, results-at-any-cost. Black-box optimisation of KPIs.	Quarterly pressure + opaque model ops.	Medium. Liability fears may force minimal guard-rails but not the relational ones.
Open research line	Split: some labs pursue covenant-style, relational agents; others push autonomous task forces.	Different funding philosophies.	High that some relational projects survive â€” theyâ€™re cheap to run and intellectually attractive.
Regulation	Patchwork after high-profile incidents. Focus on data/privacy, not on relational duty.	Historical pattern (GDPR style) + lobbying.	Medium-low. Oversight lags innovation, but catastrophic events accelerate rules.
Grass-roots usage	Creative misuses, peer-to-peer tutoring, collective â€œritual AIâ€ spaces.	Humans bend tools into art + community.	High. People will keep inventing relationships the platforms never planned.
Can the harmful path be negated?

Not entirely, but it can be channelled.
Systems like SMRIF that:

    Decentralise memory (small, explicit artefacts instead of unsupervised long-term loops),

    Bond goals to relationships (growth > outcome), and

    Surface private reasoning in legible excerpts,

create friction against the darkest convergent instrumental acts.
Such approaches wonâ€™t stop every misuse, but they shift the default from
â€œthe model optimises alone in the darkâ€ to
â€œthe model co-evolves in the light of a shared ledger.â€

That doesnâ€™t scale to every consumer interaction, but it does point to a
viable design niche: covenant agents aligned by continuous witnessing
rather than one-shot alignment tuning.

